1
00:00:11,067 --> 00:00:11,867
<i> Dead!</i>

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,033
<i> There's a dead person here!</i>

3
00:00:13,167 --> 00:00:14,400
<i> Call the police!</i>

4
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:17,600
<i>The body of Brando Salazar,
also known as Daga, was found.</i>

5
00:00:17,733 --> 00:00:19,867
<i>That's why I filed a libel case
against him,</i>

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,533
<i> so I can prove to everyone</i>

7
00:00:21,667 --> 00:00:24,567
<i>that this is a demolition job
against me.</i>

8
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:25,467
<i> Boss!</i>

9
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,033
<i>How was your meeting
with Victor?</i>

10
00:00:27,167 --> 00:00:29,567
<i>He believes that the Mayor is
still the one who is responsible</i>

11
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:30,867
<i>for everything that is happening
to him.</i>

12
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,267
<i>Your father is very indebted
to you, Boss.</i>

13
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:34,733
<i>because he will win this
election.</i>

14
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:35,600
<i> Don't worry.</i>

15
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:38,100
<i> Everyone who owes me will pay.</i>

16
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:42,233
<i>Enriquez, Tonyo is a smart cop.</i>

17
00:00:42,367 --> 00:00:45,767
<i> And Amo, being his father,</i>

18
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:47,333
<i>has nothing to do with the cases
we're handling.</i>

19
00:00:47,467 --> 00:00:48,467
<i> Our condolences.</i>

20
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:52,200
<i>We're here to help you find out
who killed Daga.</i>

21
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,767
<i> Trust me, Buddy.</i>

22
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:55,200
<i> You are not my Buddy.</i>

23
00:00:55,333 --> 00:00:57,800
<i>We won't let you go without
getting revenge!</i>

24
00:00:57,933 --> 00:00:59,533
<i> You'll pay for this!</i>

25
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:47,000
Sir, let's go!

26
00:02:21,567 --> 00:02:22,900
Now that Daga is gone,

27
00:02:23,033 --> 00:02:27,300
how can I prove that he's just
slandering me, right?

28
00:02:27,433 --> 00:02:30,667
And that's the statement
from our mayoral candidate,

29
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:32,333
Victor Santiago.

30
00:02:32,467 --> 00:02:36,700
This is after the gang leader
Brando Salazar,

31
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:39,467
better known as Daga,
was found dead.

32
00:02:41,533 --> 00:02:42,833
Are you okay?

33
00:02:42,967 --> 00:02:44,000
Ma'am Selena...

34
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:54,467
Hey, there's Amo!

35
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:57,233
He's the one who planned
the chaos at the fiesta!

36
00:02:57,367 --> 00:02:58,467
He's a murderer!

37
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,133
Amo!

38
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:04,233
- Murderer!
- Murderer!

39
00:03:07,367 --> 00:03:10,800
- Murderer!
- Murderer!

40
00:03:14,667 --> 00:03:16,000
- Murderer!
- Murderer!

41
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:18,867
- That's enough!
- What are you waiting for?

42
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:22,067
- Murderer!
- Murderer!

43
00:03:22,233 --> 00:03:26,067
- Stop it!
- Get off from there!

44
00:03:30,567 --> 00:03:31,267
Sir...

45
00:03:32,467 --> 00:03:33,333
Ma'am?

46
00:03:33,467 --> 00:03:35,600
Sir, I know we've discussed
this before,

47
00:03:35,733 --> 00:03:39,000
but I'm going to ask you again.

48
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:40,967
Please let me make a phone call.

49
00:03:42,167 --> 00:03:44,667
Okay, Ma'am,
but this is how it goes.

50
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:48,500
You can't not tell me
who you want to talk to.

51
00:03:48,633 --> 00:03:49,933
Sir, believe me.

52
00:03:50,067 --> 00:03:51,967
She's not really a threat
to my life.

53
00:03:53,067 --> 00:03:56,600
If it's not a threat,
why won't you tell us?

54
00:03:56,767 --> 00:03:59,100
Because, Ma'am, I don't want her
to get involved either.

55
00:03:59,233 --> 00:04:01,400
So many people have already been
involved because of me.

56
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:05,267
I'm begging you,
please help me.

57
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,533
I'm just going to talk to her,
even if it's just for a moment.

58
00:04:14,733 --> 00:04:17,167
Sir, Sir Tonyo and I are
the only ones

59
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:18,867
who know where Daga is hiding.

60
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,700
If it's really a police officer
who took him away,

61
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:21,367
then that means...

62
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:22,433
Enriquez...

63
00:04:22,567 --> 00:04:24,767
Can you stop thinking about it?

64
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:25,767
I already know that.

65
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:30,133
Who knows, Daga met with another
police officer?

66
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:32,467
Don't doubt Tonyo.

67
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:38,533
Whether it's Lieutenant Conde
or another police officer

68
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:40,233
who they're saying is with Daga,

69
00:04:41,267 --> 00:04:43,633
that means there's a mole
in our station.

70
00:04:43,767 --> 00:04:46,367
Enriquez,
the important thing is,

71
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,867
let's just discuss everything
with Chief when we get back.

72
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:49,767
Bok...

73
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:51,300
Bok.

74
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,733
Sir Tonyo, what are you doing
here?

75
00:04:55,867 --> 00:04:56,900
Chief said you're going to talk

76
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:58,967
to the other members of Daga's
gang,

77
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,767
so I followed you here.

78
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:02,600
What?

79
00:05:02,733 --> 00:05:03,733
Have you talked to them yet?

80
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:06,933
Yes, we've talked to them.

81
00:05:07,067 --> 00:05:08,833
But the important thing now is,

82
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:11,500
buy me a soda because,

83
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:14,100
well, I got tired from running.

84
00:05:15,167 --> 00:05:16,833
I'll tell you all about it.

85
00:05:16,967 --> 00:05:18,733
I passed by a store over there.

86
00:05:18,867 --> 00:05:20,100
Is there one there?
That's perfect!

87
00:05:25,767 --> 00:05:26,567
Hello?

88
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:27,633
Ma'am Bobby!

89
00:05:27,767 --> 00:05:29,133
Ma'am, Bobby, this is Selena.

90
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:29,900
Selena?

91
00:05:30,033 --> 00:05:31,000
I'm sorry...

92
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:31,767
I know...

93
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:32,767
I know I'm not allowed to call,

94
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:36,233
but you're the only one
I really trust.

95
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:38,333
I have something important
to tell you.

96
00:05:38,467 --> 00:05:40,000
Why, Selena? What happened?

97
00:05:40,133 --> 00:05:41,367
I just remembered now.

98
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:45,133
Sonny mentioned to me
that Amo has a connection

99
00:05:45,267 --> 00:05:46,433
to the police force.

100
00:05:46,567 --> 00:05:51,600
Then he said that person
is someone Amo really trusts.

101
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:52,867
Be careful.

102
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:56,333
<i>Why didn't you say that
the person of interest in</i>

103
00:05:56,467 --> 00:05:58,300
<i>the cases we're investigating
is your father?</i>

104
00:05:58,433 --> 00:06:01,667
<i>If you want to waste time
on gossip,</i>

105
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,667
<i> don't involve me in it.</i>

106
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,733
<i> I have work to do.</i>

107
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:08,633
Do you like soft drinks?
What soft drinks do you like?

108
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:12,233
No, Sir. I'm fine.

109
00:06:12,367 --> 00:06:13,833
I told you she doesn't drink
sodas.

110
00:06:13,967 --> 00:06:14,633
Let's go.

111
00:06:20,467 --> 00:06:20,967
Bok!

112
00:06:31,633 --> 00:06:34,300
Bobby, are you really serious?

113
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:38,933
Do you think Sir Tonyo
is Amo's spy?

114
00:06:40,533 --> 00:06:43,400
After all,
they're father and son.

115
00:06:43,567 --> 00:06:46,300
But why would he do that?

116
00:06:46,433 --> 00:06:48,767
Do you think he's the one
who killed Daga?

117
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:50,667
I'm not sure.

118
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:55,100
All I know is, if there
are too many coincidences,

119
00:06:55,233 --> 00:06:57,300
it's no longer a coincidence.

120
00:06:57,433 --> 00:07:01,700
But can he do that when
Sir Tonyo is so kind?

121
00:07:03,433 --> 00:07:04,200
Wait,

122
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:08,200
if Amo is really the mastermind,

123
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:14,833
Tonyo is the one to blame for
his girlfriend's death.

124
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,900
Grandmother,
what should I do?

125
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:20,900
Bobby, be careful what you say,

126
00:07:21,033 --> 00:07:25,833
especially to your colleagues
and especially to Tonyo,

127
00:07:25,967 --> 00:07:33,967
or else that might ruin
your career.

128
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,800
Don't forget to report to me,
okay?

129
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:36,567
Yes, Sir.

130
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:37,667
Update me.

131
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:38,567
Copy it.

132
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:41,700
Okay.

133
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:44,800
Chief...

134
00:07:44,933 --> 00:07:46,567
- Enriquez?
- Can I talk to you?

135
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:47,600
Perfect timing, Enriquez.

136
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:50,200
Conde and I talked about
the strategy

137
00:07:50,333 --> 00:07:53,167
based on the information you
and Garcia gathered yesterday.

138
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:55,000
Chief, can we talk just the two
of us?

139
00:08:00,733 --> 00:08:01,800
Okay, follow me.

140
00:08:10,467 --> 00:08:11,733
What's the problem, Enriquez?

141
00:08:14,067 --> 00:08:15,367
Sir,

142
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:18,967
you heard what Lieutenant Garcia
said about Daga.

143
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,700
Yes, that's right.

144
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:26,633
But there are many more angles
to consider.

145
00:08:26,767 --> 00:08:30,567
That's what Conde and I were
talking about earlier.

146
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:33,333
Maybe the person who went
and killed Daga

147
00:08:33,467 --> 00:08:35,433
just pretended to be a police
officer.

148
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:39,733
Did you find out where
Lieutenant Conde was last night?

149
00:08:39,867 --> 00:08:41,467
What are you talking about,
Enriquez?

150
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,633
Chief, I spoke to Selena
yesterday.

151
00:08:43,767 --> 00:08:47,033
Sonny mentioned that Amo had
a henchman here at the station.

152
00:08:47,167 --> 00:08:48,000
What?

153
00:08:48,133 --> 00:08:50,800
Sir, according to Daga's
companion,

154
00:08:50,933 --> 00:08:53,167
a policeman took Daga away
last night.

155
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:56,767
Sir, Lieutenant Conde
and I are the only ones

156
00:08:56,933 --> 00:08:58,367
who know where Daga is hiding.

157
00:08:58,500 --> 00:08:59,600
Just tell me straight.

158
00:09:00,767 --> 00:09:01,900
What are you thinking?

159
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:05,700
Chief, I have a strong feeling
that Conde is Amo's henchman

160
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:07,067
here at the station.

161
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,100
What happened to you, Enriquez?

162
00:09:09,233 --> 00:09:13,533
Just because your theories
are right about Victor Santiago,

163
00:09:13,667 --> 00:09:15,200
you can think of anything...

164
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:16,100
Sir...

165
00:09:16,233 --> 00:09:17,467
Especially with your colleagues
here!

166
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,667
Sir, this is not just
based on speculation.

167
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:22,267
Lieutenant Conde
must have a reason.

168
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:23,267
Did you know

169
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:26,500
that Lieutenant Conde
is Amo's son?

170
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:27,967
That's nothing new.

171
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:30,267
You know that, Sir?

172
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:33,600
Yes, but that has nothing
to do with the investigation!

173
00:09:33,733 --> 00:09:34,867
There is!

174
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,233
That's a clear conflict
of interest, Sir!

175
00:09:40,133 --> 00:09:41,167
I think we're done here.

176
00:09:45,433 --> 00:09:46,533
Sir, yes, Sir.

177
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:50,933
Enriquez,

178
00:09:53,367 --> 00:09:54,900
get Conde in here.

179
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:59,000
And what we talked about just
now,

180
00:09:59,133 --> 00:10:00,633
can that be just between
the two of us?

181
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:01,933
Is that clear?

182
00:10:11,967 --> 00:10:13,200
Lieutenant Conde,

183
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:15,833
the Chief is calling you.

184
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,067
Are you okay, Enriquez?

185
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:24,267
Yes, of course.

186
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:26,933
The Chief is waiting
for you inside.

187
00:10:40,567 --> 00:10:43,867
Just always stick close to me.

188
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,033
Study my movements

189
00:10:46,167 --> 00:10:48,800
because I am the epitome
of a perfect police officer.

190
00:10:48,933 --> 00:10:49,900
Just stay close to me

191
00:10:50,033 --> 00:10:52,133
so you'll be blessed like you
are anointed...

192
00:10:57,367 --> 00:10:59,967
Bobby, what are you doing there?

193
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:02,133
Those looks,
I know that very well.

194
00:11:04,433 --> 00:11:06,133
You plan to go to the Chief,
don't you?

195
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:11,433
Then you will take credit
for our investigation yesterday,

196
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:12,333
right?

197
00:11:14,367 --> 00:11:16,067
Let me just make it clear
to you.

198
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:19,133
I am the lead investigator
on our team,

199
00:11:19,267 --> 00:11:20,800
so I will talk to the Chief.

200
00:11:31,167 --> 00:11:32,833
Bok, what happened?

201
00:11:32,967 --> 00:11:34,233
Bok!

202
00:11:34,367 --> 00:11:35,033
Bok!

203
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:37,500
Chief, what happened?

204
00:11:37,633 --> 00:11:40,333
What did you and Sir Tonyo
discuss?

205
00:11:40,467 --> 00:11:41,500
You're right, Enriquez.

206
00:11:42,733 --> 00:11:46,100
The integrity of the
investigation is questionable

207
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:49,967
if it ever comes out in public
that Tonyo is Victor's son,

208
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:54,133
but I'm not saying he's
an accomplice in this.

209
00:11:54,267 --> 00:11:56,433
Sir, what happened to Conde?

210
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:01,167
I suspended him indefinitely.

211
00:12:02,133 --> 00:12:02,933
What?

212
00:12:09,033 --> 00:12:10,033
Amo...

213
00:12:10,167 --> 00:12:11,767
Verns, sorry.

214
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:12,967
As for Amo,

215
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:16,300
all campaign activities
are canceled for now, okay?

216
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,533
You need something else?

217
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:23,767
There's someone outside, Amo.

218
00:12:23,900 --> 00:12:26,367
He's waiting for you.
He's looking for you.

219
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:41,333
Tonyo?

220
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:53,700
Sir Tonyo was suspended?

221
00:12:53,833 --> 00:12:56,067
Well, we won't see him here
at the station anymore.

222
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,033
Yes, Bok.

223
00:12:57,167 --> 00:12:59,333
- That's a pity.
- What's now?

224
00:12:59,467 --> 00:13:01,800
There will be fewer good
and handsome police

225
00:13:01,933 --> 00:13:02,800
at this station.

226
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:10,633
Excuse me, but the loss of Tonyo
doesn't diminish

227
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:13,333
the handsomeness of Station 12

228
00:13:13,467 --> 00:13:16,433
because he only contributed
ten percent to it.

229
00:13:16,567 --> 00:13:20,433
The 90 percent of handsomeness
is still here.

230
00:13:23,467 --> 00:13:24,300
Enriquez!

231
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:28,800
Aren't you overwhelmed
by what you're thinking?

232
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:30,033
It's deep.

233
00:13:30,167 --> 00:13:32,800
Do you feel guilty about
what happened to Tonyo, right?

234
00:13:32,933 --> 00:13:34,800
He was suspended because of you.

235
00:13:37,267 --> 00:13:40,100
Sir, I don't want Sir Tonyo
to be suspended.

236
00:13:41,167 --> 00:13:44,667
But shouldn't he be the one
to inhibit himself

237
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:46,133
from this investigation,

238
00:13:47,567 --> 00:13:50,500
especially since Amo
is his father?

239
00:13:50,633 --> 00:13:52,167
Lieutenant Conde's father
is Amo?

240
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:54,433
As in Victor Santiago?

241
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:57,067
Enriquez, look at what you're
doing.

242
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:58,333
It's spreading.

243
00:13:58,467 --> 00:14:00,433
That's why Conde is so annoyed
with you.

244
00:14:02,267 --> 00:14:06,267
Well, Sir, it's not an issue
with him, why did he hide it?

245
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:09,700
I had to suspect and do some
research to find out the truth.

246
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:10,967
Do some research?

247
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:13,600
I thought you
and Lieutenant Conde were close?

248
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:17,500
<i> We are okay now?</i>

249
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:20,400
<i> We?</i>

250
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:26,033
We're not close.

251
00:14:27,467 --> 00:14:28,700
I'll go ahead, Sir.

252
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:37,633
It's good that you came
to visit.

253
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,633
To be honest,

254
00:14:42,367 --> 00:14:44,200
I don't even know why I'm here
today.

255
00:14:45,567 --> 00:14:46,900
Is there a problem?

256
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:50,500
Let's talk inside.
Come on, come inside first.

257
00:14:50,633 --> 00:14:51,400
Come on, son.

258
00:14:57,433 --> 00:14:59,067
Just bring the motorcycle
inside, okay?

259
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,667
Okay, Sir.

260
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:01,533
Let's go.

261
00:15:08,767 --> 00:15:10,367
Son, come on in.

262
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:16,200
What do you want?
Coffee, soft drinks?

263
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:19,533
Get us some coffee.

264
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:20,633
Okay, Amo.

265
00:15:27,333 --> 00:15:28,800
I'm suspended.

266
00:15:31,433 --> 00:15:32,100
Why?

267
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:38,233
I argued with Chief
because of you.

268
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:42,567
They are accusing you of being
the mastermind

269
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:46,000
behind Daga's death,
Faye Guerrero's kidnapping,

270
00:15:47,133 --> 00:15:48,833
and the San Isidro bank robbery.

271
00:16:14,267 --> 00:16:15,767
Major Flores.

272
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:19,700
Hey!

273
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:20,700
Don't come any closer!

274
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,533
- Don't come any closer!
- Put that down!

275
00:16:23,667 --> 00:16:24,633
I said, Put that down!

276
00:16:42,067 --> 00:16:43,633
Charlie?

277
00:16:43,767 --> 00:16:44,500
Bobby...

278
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,167
What are you doing here
at our station?

279
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:56,133
Lieutenant Charlie Samson.

280
00:16:57,367 --> 00:16:58,667
Welcome to Station 12.

281
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,000
Thank you.

282
00:17:00,133 --> 00:17:02,533
Enriquez,
you guys are batchmates.

283
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:06,367
They're here because they need
our help

284
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:07,833
with a case they're handling.

285
00:17:09,233 --> 00:17:13,433
By the way, that's his partner,
Lieutenant Sandro Paloma.

286
00:17:13,567 --> 00:17:14,167
Sir.

287
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:17,967
We're here because we're
investigating human trafficking.

288
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:20,233
Our lead brought us here
to Calabari.

289
00:17:20,367 --> 00:17:22,833
My niece almost fell victim
to it a while ago.

290
00:17:22,967 --> 00:17:26,433
So, Enriquez,
if you find any leads,

291
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:29,100
please let Lieutenant Samson
know immediately.

292
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:31,800
Yes, Chief.

293
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:36,267
Lieutenant Paloma,
let's talk in my office.

294
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:37,233
Yes, Sir.

295
00:17:42,367 --> 00:17:43,600
Bobby,

296
00:17:43,733 --> 00:17:47,633
weren't you the best
in our class back then?

297
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,767
Why are you still a sergeant?

298
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:52,567
Are you asking questions
or teasing?

299
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:53,967
Calm down, Bobby.

300
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:55,133
I'm just curious.

301
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:59,600
I heard you transferred
to Station 12.

302
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:00,033
Why?

303
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:03,700
Maybe you made a mess
at Station 11?

304
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:05,433
I transferred to Station 12

305
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:07,633
because I wanted to solve
the death of my Godmother.

306
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:09,733
She's also a police officer.

307
00:18:09,867 --> 00:18:11,367
Have you solved it yet?

308
00:18:13,233 --> 00:18:16,167
Until now, you still haven't
moved on from what happened

309
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:17,200
to us at the academy?

310
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:18,733
That's been a while.

311
00:18:18,867 --> 00:18:20,700
How did that come into our
conversation?

312
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:21,933
Or maybe you.

313
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:23,900
Maybe you're the one who hasn't
moved on yet.

314
00:18:26,367 --> 00:18:27,800
Are you just going to turn
your back on me?

315
00:18:29,167 --> 00:18:30,933
Don't you know how to respect?

316
00:18:41,133 --> 00:18:42,867
Park my motorcycle.

317
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:43,767
Be careful with it,

318
00:18:44,967 --> 00:18:46,767
Sergeant Enriquez.

319
00:19:01,667 --> 00:19:03,233
Lieutenant seems to be picking
on you.

320
00:19:07,433 --> 00:19:09,667
They should have accused me

321
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,433
as the one who killed Ninoy
and John Lennon.

322
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:15,633
I'm serious.

323
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:18,333
I defended you to my co-workers.

324
00:19:18,467 --> 00:19:20,100
That's why I want to know

325
00:19:22,067 --> 00:19:24,467
if everything you said
when we talked was true.

326
00:19:26,133 --> 00:19:28,833
<i> Tonyo, is there a problem?</i>

327
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:33,067
<i>Just make sure everything you
answer my question is true.</i>

328
00:19:34,133 --> 00:19:35,767
<i> If not, we'll end up fighting.</i>

329
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:37,500
<i> Is this about Daga?</i>

330
00:19:37,633 --> 00:19:41,333
<i>You know, Son, they're just
trying to ruin my name.</i>

331
00:19:41,467 --> 00:19:43,267
<i> This is not about him.</i>

332
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:48,000
<i>This is about the museum robbery
and the San Isidro bank robbery.</i>

333
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:51,167
<i>Did you have anything
to do with that?</i>

334
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:55,933
<i> I'll have my fingers cut off</i>

335
00:19:56,067 --> 00:19:58,667
<i>if you discover that I had
anything to do with it.</i>

336
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:00,567
Tonyo,

337
00:20:01,933 --> 00:20:05,567
whatever I said before,
nothing has changed.

338
00:20:05,700 --> 00:20:08,200
I had nothing to do
with all of that.

339
00:20:10,367 --> 00:20:12,700
Thank you very much
for defending me.

340
00:20:16,567 --> 00:20:21,067
I just want to make sure that
I'm defending the right person.

341
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:26,167
I'll bet my candidacy

342
00:20:28,033 --> 00:20:30,300
that it was right for you
to believe in me.

343
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,900
I know we're not close,

344
00:20:42,767 --> 00:20:44,633
but I also know you're not
a bad person.

345
00:20:46,267 --> 00:20:47,167
Thanks, Son.

346
00:20:48,467 --> 00:20:50,267
That's a big deal to me.

347
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:52,100
You may not be a bad person,

348
00:20:53,633 --> 00:20:55,667
but you were still a bad father.

349
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:58,333
I know.

350
00:21:00,067 --> 00:21:01,400
I can't change that.

351
00:21:02,667 --> 00:21:03,933
But I want to make up.

352
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:06,467
You want to make up?

353
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:09,100
Okay.

354
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:14,933
Give me a job.

355
00:21:16,267 --> 00:21:17,700
Make me your bodyguard.

356
00:21:22,567 --> 00:21:23,300
Thank you.

357
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:31,133
You can have it.

358
00:21:34,367 --> 00:21:36,700
Did you know that it was
Sergeant Enriquez's fault

359
00:21:36,833 --> 00:21:38,300
that his godmother died?

360
00:21:38,433 --> 00:21:39,667
Since when have you been
interested in the lives

361
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:40,833
of other police officers?

362
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:42,533
And from a different station?

363
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:46,167
Anything about Bobby Enriquez,
I'm interested.

364
00:21:47,233 --> 00:21:48,300
I know the story.

365
00:21:49,333 --> 00:21:51,267
- It wasn't her fault when...
- She stole something from me.

366
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:53,733
My bag!

367
00:21:53,867 --> 00:21:55,700
Let's talk later about
Sergeant Enriquez later.

368
00:21:55,833 --> 00:21:57,467
These guys are fools.

369
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:58,567
I'll take care of them.

370
00:21:58,700 --> 00:21:59,700
Finish that.

371
00:22:03,933 --> 00:22:08,300
Help!

372
00:22:08,433 --> 00:22:10,733
Help! My bag!

373
00:22:10,867 --> 00:22:12,333
Thieves!

374
00:22:32,467 --> 00:22:34,533
It's exciting here in Calabari.

375
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:37,267
Should I transfer to Station 12?

376
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:38,833
Seriously?

377
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:42,467
I want Enriquez and me
to be close again like before.

378
00:22:46,667 --> 00:22:49,933
Sir Tonyo, Sir, Amo just needs
to talk to me.

379
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:52,333
He said he'll get back to you.

380
00:22:52,467 --> 00:22:54,667
If you need anything,
Sir, just let me know.

381
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:56,567
- Yeah, feel at home.
- Thank you. Okay.

382
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:13,300
Who are you?

383
00:23:16,733 --> 00:23:17,933
You're a cop!

384
00:23:58,867 --> 00:24:00,400
Tonyo!

385
00:24:00,533 --> 00:24:01,500
That's enough!

386
00:24:02,967 --> 00:24:05,633
That's Roman,
my head of security.

387
00:24:05,767 --> 00:24:07,967
Roman, that's Tonyo, my son.

388
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:20,567
You were great earlier.

389
00:24:20,700 --> 00:24:22,067
I almost lost my breath.

390
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:24,700
I'm sure your mother
is proud of you.

391
00:24:24,833 --> 00:24:26,233
My mother is gone.

392
00:24:26,367 --> 00:24:28,067
Dad and I are not okay
because of you!

393
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:31,667
Your greetings won't make up
for the loss of our mother.

394
00:24:31,833 --> 00:24:32,933
What do you think of him?

395
00:24:33,067 --> 00:24:34,433
He's still acting like
a police officer.

396
00:24:34,567 --> 00:24:37,567
He could just be working,
or he could be investigating.

397
00:24:37,700 --> 00:24:41,867
Don't be offended by my hiring
of Tonyo as my bodyguard.

398
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:45,667
Just say you took advantage of
Lieutenant Conde's suspension!

399
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:46,833
Enriquez,

400
00:24:46,967 --> 00:24:48,200
that's why I got suspended,
right, because of you?

401
00:24:48,333 --> 00:24:50,233
And now, you're going
to insult my father.
